    "stac_version": "1.1.0",
    "description": "SST4 provides sea surface temperature retrieved from the mid-wave IR bands near 4 \u00b5m (\u223c3.7\u20134.1 \u00b5m). These channels are typically used at night (to avoid solar contamination) and can offer reduced sensitivity to atmospheric water vapor compared with long-wave (11/12 \u00b5m) split-window SST, making SST4 a valuable complement in humid or tropical conditions. \n\n Geophysical variables in this suite include:\n\u2022 bias_sst4 \u2014 4 \u00b5m Sea Surface Temperature bias (\u00b0C)\n\u2022 flags_sst4 \u2014 Product-specific flags, 4 \u00b5m Sea Surface Temperature (integer bitmask)\n\u2022 l2_flags \u2014 Level-2 Processing Flags (integer bitmask; see bit definitions)\n\u2022 qual_sst4 \u2014 Quality levels for 4 \u00b5m Sea Surface Temperature (integer quality flag) \n\u2022 sst4 \u2014 4 \u00b5m Sea Surface Temperature (\u00b0C) \n\u2022 sstref \u2014 Sea Surface Temperature reference (\u00b0C)\n\u2022 stdv_sst4 \u2014 4 \u00b5m Sea Surface Temperature standard deviatio (\u00b0C\n",
